I'm SUPER afraid of needles and Baron made me feel so comfortable. I got my first tattoo so that I could have visible scars to match the invisible ones. He custom designed a tattoo for me in remembrance of my deceased family members and it was everything that I imagined it to be.

<text>I stumbled upon Monkey Face Tattoos & shop owner Baron Davis by accident after deciding to have a sleeve worked on. Clearly on display is some of his portfolios on display for review in order to showcase his legitimacy and achievements throughout his professional career. <review>I took a group of friends (not from the Bay Area) to Bootie last night (2-20-10) and we had a blast. We arrived a little before 1am. There was no line and the cover was $12. The music was great and we danced until 3am! I love the music and I love the layout of the club. There is a second floor where you can view the whole dance floor from above and a separate room that played trance type music. There are side boxes that allowed people (girls and guys) dance on and the stage area was open for everyone to dance on, which I thought was very fun as well. Over all my friends and I had a great time and really enjoyed the music. The only negative thing I can say is that the bathroom was very dirty. I know it is hard to maintain but there was water (at least I hope it was water) all over the floor.</review>< Pics>

This place was completely empty on a Friday night.

I ordered a vodka tonic($13) and it was mostly tonic.The bartender was looking up the recipe on her phone before making the drink. Not a good sign . She actually looked up all our drink orders except for the vodka redbull. .
Btw, if you order a whiskey coke, you will be charged for the coke separately ($5 coke).

DJ was cool but because it was empty you could tell he wasn't enjoying it. At one point he left his set and left a playlist playing. He was still there but went to grab drinks at the bar LOL. I don't blame him though it was boring.</review>

< review>
I've been to over a dozen different dance clubs as a twentysomething. Most of the time, I don't really enjoy clubs because of the terrible music unless I've had several drinks. However, Bootie is by far my favorite dance event. The music appeals to different crowds. You'll hear mashups from today's top 40 with classic rock, 80s pop, and even Rebecca Black. If you hate clubs, you may like Bootie so I suggest you give it a try.</review>

This is a little local gem. The decor is older, but that's more than made up for by the delicious traditional food at reasonable prices.  We enjoyed plenty of large, fresh pieces of sushi and an eel roll for $25.
We saw that most of the clientele was Japanese.  That tells us that the food must be authentic.
We've found that this part of Marina is rich in wonderful ethnic restaurants - Japanese,  Thai,  Vietnamese and Chinese.  It's worth the trip to Marina.</Review>

1513343200236< /Date>

< review>
We like New Tokyo. It's a mom and pop shop. Mom does the sushi out front while her male partner waits tables and collects the bills.
One or two cooks work the back.
The prices for sushi and entrees in general are inexpensive when compared against other Japanese cuisine elsewhere on the Monterey Peninsula.
$3.25 California Roll as an example.
They are definitely a neighborhood eatery and don't seem to reach out to tourists. Maybe 12 tables inside.
I ding one star because the front door and windows could use a windex treatment now and then. The food tastes good though and that is what really matters.<//review>

< Name>
Richard Leonard</Name>
<Date>1619094946827</Date><Rating>5< /Rating>< review>
I NEVER thought that I would write a review in which I say "It's a pleasure to go to the dentist." But here goes -- a visit to Dr. Zadeh's office is a pleasure!

So what are the underlying facts? It's a combination of a welcoming environment and a genuine friendliness that extends from the appointment reminder calls from Debbie and her welcome upon arrival at the office, to all staff, including Dr. Zadeh.

Together with the welcoming vibe (and excellent music playlist), Dr. Zadeh displays an authentic interest in her patients' lives and offers a caring disposition (she asked several times during a recent procedure "Are you okay" and "Doing okay?"). And when it comes to her technical expertise, she has "the touch." I had a filling yesterday, and didn't feel the needle when she numbed me up. Beyond that, the general health of my teeth and gums has improved under her care over the last year-plus, and that included some no-pressure suggestions from her about how I might better care for things in-between visits.

(Add to that, it's a low pressure office...no attempt to "upsell" me on products and procedures . There is nothing more uncomfortable than to have a health care provider arrogantly tell you that you might "NEED" something that's going to pay for his/her kid's college education.)

I am comfortable offering an unconditional recommendation of Dr. Zadeh's dental office!< /review>

<UserId.>115274363073867340845</UserId.><text>Great dentist very polite very professionally</text></record></dataset><record>
<user>102103986599666335159< /user>< review>
First off, I've had a long history and an extremely positive experience with Dr. Zadeh's dental group over the years, initially as a patient of Dr. Robin Sera who recently retired from her practice. From the beginning (over 25 years ago), the entire staff brought me in and treated me like family. When I moved to San Diego, there was no way I going anywhere else for my dental care. My friends, family and coworkers often ask why I drive so far for my dental appointments and I tell them the same thing every time, "I'll fly in from the far corners of the earth if I have to in order to go to the only place I trust for my dental care". After meeting with Dr. Zadeh earlier this year, I was immediately impressed with her professionalism, knowledge, confidence and overall demeanor. I knew right away that she was someone I could trust. She clearly studied my entire dental history prior to my first visit which made me feel extremely comfortable right off the bat. What struck me most was how much time and care she took to talk with me about my dental history and to genuinely get to know me as a person. When you talk to her, she's 100% focused and tuned-in and listens to every word you have to say. That's a big deal to me, especially when you're getting to know your Dr.! Needless to say, my first experience with Dr. Zadeh was very positive.
Following my cleaning and check-up, I was diagnosed as needing to have one of my wisdom teeth extracted which I scheduled a couple of months later. Since I've never had a tooth extracted before, I was in unfamiliar territory. However, based on my first visit with Dr. Zadeh, I knew I was in good hands. I want to thank her and her amazing team for taking care of me on the day of my procedure. Her dental skills were extremely evident and appreciated as I never once felt any discomfort or pain throughout the extraction. She talked me through each step and explained everything she was doing along the way, always making sure I was ok. I'm someone who appreciates the details when it comes to technical procedures and Dr. Zadeh was more than happy to provide me with the step-by-step breakdown of what was going on. She was focused, methodical and extremely confident throughout the entire procedure. In addition, I appreciated her personal phone call later that day to check in on me, with additional calls that came in from her team over the next couple of days. I highly recommend Dr. Zadeh for anyone who's looking for an exceptional, highly professional and caring dentist. I'm definitely coming back!<//review>

martk fartkerson< /name>
< text>
Our favorite Thai food reataurant!  Everything on the menu is excellent.  It's served family style, so order 2 or 3 things and share.  We usually get a rice dish, a curry dish, and a noodle dish.  Then we take home whatevers left and have dinner for another night.  Definitely worth getting more than just a single entre per person.  Variety is the key.  The food is as spicy as you want, but you may wish to start low spice and then add more as you go until it's just right.  Thai spices are powerful!< /text>
